.TH COUNTRY-BLOCK 8 "May 2026" "country-block" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
country-block \- manage country-based firewall blocking
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B country-block
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B country-block
maintains ipsets from country IP block lists and applies iptables and
ip6tables rules based on
.IR /etc/country-block/rules.conf .
.PP
The command must be run as root when changing firewall state.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B apply
Restore cached ipsets from
.I /var/cache/country-block/ipsets.save
and apply firewall rules from the rules file.
.TP
.B update
Download current country IP block lists for the configured countries and
refresh
.IR /var/cache/country-block/ipsets.save .
This command does not change live firewall rules.
.TP
.B sync
Run
.B country-block update
and then
.BR "country-block apply" .
.TP
.B status
Show a read-only summary of the rules file, saved ipset cache, downloaded
lists, live managed firewall rules, and systemd unit state. The command exits
successfully even when it reports warnings or inconsistencies.
.TP
.B clear
Remove live iptables and ip6tables rules managed by
.BR country-block .
Downloaded lists and the saved ipset cache are left in place.
.TP
.B try
Prepare any missing ipsets for
.IR /etc/country-block/rules.conf ,
downloading country lists if needed, and temporarily apply its rules. The
previous iptables and ip6tables state is saved before rules are tested. If
confirmed, the rules are kept. Otherwise, the previous firewall state is
restored.
.TP
.B try --config FILE
Prepare any missing candidate ipsets, downloading country lists if needed, and
temporarily apply rules from a candidate rules file. If confirmed, the rules
are kept active. The candidate file is not installed. Otherwise, the previous
firewall state is restored.
.TP
.B edit
Copy
.I /etc/country-block/rules.conf
to a temporary file, open it with
.IR EDITOR " or " nano ,
and run the same temporary confirmation flow as
.BR try .
If confirmed, the edited temporary file is installed as
.IR /etc/country-block/rules.conf .
This is the recommended interactive workflow on remote machines.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "--config " FILE
Candidate rules file for
.BR try .
When omitted,
.B try
uses
.IR /etc/country-block/rules.conf .
.TP
.BI "--timeout " SECONDS
Confirmation timeout for
.B try
or
.BR edit .
The default is 120 seconds.
.SH SYSTEMD UNITS
.TP
.B country-block.service
Runs
.B country-block apply
during boot to restore cached ipsets and firewall rules. It is installed
disabled by default so package installation and upgrades do not apply firewall
rules automatically. Enable it only after confirming the configured rules work.
.TP
.B country-block.timer
Runs weekly and triggers
.BR country-block-update.service .
It is installed disabled and stopped by default so package installation and
upgrades do not refresh or apply rules automatically. Enable it only if
automatic live updates are wanted.
.TP
.B country-block-update.service
Oneshot helper used by
.BR country-block.timer .
It runs
.B country-block sync
to refresh the saved ipset cache and apply the updated firewall rules.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/country-block/rules.conf
Country, chain, and IP-version rules.
.TP
.I /var/cache/country-block/
Downloaded country lists and saved ipset state.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ipset (8),
.BR iptables (8),
.BR ip6tables (8),
.BR curl (1)
